gn=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 9:46:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2076.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 4 style chain (hamstring &amp; friends) post patch...</span><hr size=1> * warning * the following is very vague info going on memory.  If you want exact number info test it out and log the stuff, i kinda forgot to &gt;_&lt;.  Numbers listed are noteworthy numbers that stood out while i reviewed each fight.<br><br>Tested it out about 20 times (using the evade chain only to kill the mobs), mostly on green mobs at the barrows entrance, and a few blues deeper in, here are come observations (using ellyll rapier, 16.2 / 2.4 100condition.  No specific numbers because i forgot to log them /oops!):<br><br>Hamstring hits a LOT harder than it used to.  Dont have any numbers, but this leads to the next one...<br><br>Leeper / rib separation / ripper did not seem to get as drastic of an increase as hamstring did.  The problem i had when testing this was that the damage (using 47 thrust) dealt on these 4 styles was soo inconsistant that there almost appeared to be no difference between them except the effect.<br><br>On several occassions, Hamstring hit for more leeper (and visa versa).  The fluctuation in damage between these two styles made them each seem to have a 50/50 chance of outdamaging eachother.  The highest hamstring i hit for was around 145.  Had a leeper hit harder than that, but on average they appeared to do similar damage.<br><br>Rib separation seemed to be pretty stable.  It did not jump like previous styles, and sat at a nice consistant damage rate,  usually more than ripper.  Whether or not it did more damage than leeper / hamstring would depend on how hard the they had hit the mob.  Usually it had / has high end leeper damage or more, but not always.<br><br>Ripper outdamaged rip seperation on 1 mob.  Other than that it was slightly less damage for the rest of them.<br><br>On one of the blue mobs i tested these on, they all hit between 90-110.<br><br>*things to check*<br>Check pincer.  Was playing around with greys before testing this to see what kinda bumpage garrot got, and decided to try pincer.  Pincer did more damage to the grey than garrot (but less than achellies).  Garrot did seem to get a nice bump, as it now hits harder than pierce (29 albion thrust style - used to hit harder than garrot) on these same mobs.  Test these out if you question the validity of testing damage caps and calculating what will have a higher average on greys, I am not going to make any claims that this is how things are.  It does appear that pincer got a higher damage cap though.<br><br>My perf remained the same, didnt check SS and CD out.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udrdec0y.showPublicProfile?language=EN>drDec0y</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 9:49:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2076.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> bleh</span><hr size=1> may I ask what your template is currently? and what level you are? because 145 damage on a green mob sounds real low, I know I do about 250 damage on green luch hunters in emain. . . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usirsameth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SirSameth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 10:03:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2076.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 4 style chain (hamstring &amp; friends) post patch...</span><hr size=1> I didn't notice a big difference in hamstring. I soloed a couple blues after the patch, and it did seem that garrote/AH did a bit more damage (especially AH), but Hamstring seemed the same to me.<br><br>Btw is Pincer still worth using?? I haven't used it once since I got garrote, it began to do crap for dmg and you always had to be on the side...<br><br>Sameth<br>Level 31 Infiltrator<br>Galahad <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 12:58:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2076.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> I have 50 (+5 for 55) CS and 37 ( +10 for 47) weapon spec at level 50.<br><br>The weapon is 2.4 delay also, which affects damage per hit (I can do 2hamstrings off of one evade though) in a more negative way than if i was using my slower 3.5<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ebullition>Ebullition</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 2:31:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2076.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> At level 48 with 48 in sword and 48 in crit strike, I found that Hamstring now does about about 40 more damage per hit, and Leaper now does the same damage as Stunning Stab.<br><br>In fact Hamstring/Leaper does just a little less damage for me than Creeping Death/Stunning Stab.<br><br>Hamstring/Leaper is now a GREAT chain.<br><br>Garrote and Achilles Heel are also doing much better damage, a siginificant increase!  However, the endurance it takes to power those moves is NOT worth it to me.<br><br>I still use Assault/Ice Storm (sword moves) because I can get a LOT more hits in before my endurance is gone.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 2:37:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2076.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> i find myself using garrot a lot these days (and achellies)<br>because of the lack of useful albion thrust styles, the new damage is nice (better than thrust), and the snare effect.  it is an endurance hog though, in pve groups i just use pierce(its like ghettobackstab without stealth and void of 200ish damage) or pincer.<br><br>Nice thing about the chain is that it is soo long, i find that i evade in the middle and can just start over again and have an endless loop of evade type styles, <br><br>Ripper definitly needs something done to it, its really the exact same thing as leeper damagewise.  Even has the same bleed.  Not quite worth the 50 skillpoints invested, or the prerequisite to actually executing it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td a